Core dev tools

Python 3.10+ (recommended) + venv
Git (version control)
Docker + Docker Compose (run MongoDB/PostgreSQL locally consistently)
VS Code (or your preferred IDE)

Datastores

MongoDB: raw, unstructured logs (Week 1)
PostgreSQL: summaries + metadata (Week 2)

Python libraries you’ll use
Week 1

pymongo (MongoDB client) — insert raw logs using insert_one() (MongoDB docs show usage) [mongodb.com], [pymongo.re...thedocs.io]
apscheduler (scheduling ingestion jobs) — BlockingScheduler runs in foreground and blocks on start() [apschedule...thedocs.io]
(Optional) watchdog if you want file system event-based ingestion instead of interval schedule (suggestion)

Week 2

LLM SDKs:

AWS Bedrock: boto3 + Bedrock Runtime InvokeModel [docs.aws.amazon.com], [docs.aws.amazon.com]
GCP Gemini: either google-cloud-aiplatform (Vertex AI Generative SDK) or google-genai (new unified SDK) [cloud.google.com], [docs.cloud...google.com], [googleapis.github.io]


psycopg2 or asyncpg (Postgres client)
pydantic (data models & validation)
(Optional) tiktoken or heuristic chunking

Week 3

fastapi + uvicorn (API server) — FastAPI recommends running with an ASGI server like Uvicorn; FastAPI provides fastapi run as well [fastapi.tiangolo.com]
(Optional) RAG libs like LangChain — not required for POC; you can do simple retrieval manually (suggestion)
